A SCOTS holidaymaker who had an altercation with two frail pensioners on an allinclusive <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruise_ship" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruise_ship" target="_blank">cruise</a> told <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police_officer" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Police_officer" target="_blank">police</a> he was acting in selfdefenceGraeme Finlay 53 denies unlawfully wounding Ron Phillips 70 who walks with a crutch and was carrying two cocoas for him and his 68yearold <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wife" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wife" target="_blank">wife</a> JuneFinlay of Meadowside Quay <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walking" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walking" target="_blank">Walk</a> Glasgow also denies causing <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grievous_bodily_harm" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grievous_bodily_harm" target="_blank">grievous bodily harm</a> to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/June_28" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/June_28" target="_blank">June</a> while they were <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruising_for_sex" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cruising_for_sex" target="_blank">cruising</a> off Lanzarote in January 2014Ron suffered a gash to the forehead when he was repeatedly punched and knocked out while his <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wife" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wife" target="_blank">wife</a> was later found to have fractured two vertebrae after being shoved and losing consciousness Teesside Crown Court heardThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jury" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jury" target="_blank">jury</a> heard that <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ron_Swanson" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ron_Swanson" target="_blank">Ron</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/June_28" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/June_28" target="_blank">June</a> had enjoyed dinner and gone to a cabaret bar on the ship the